VERIFICATION OF HOUSEHOLD ELIGIBILITY; REQUIRED CERTIFICATIONS (§ 14-2213)
    In order to be eligible to rent or purchase an Inclusionary Unit, a Householdhall provide to the Owner of the Inclusionary Unit a Declaration of Eligibilitynd a Certification of Income, Affordability, and Housing Size.
    Except as set forth in § 2208.1(a), an Owner shall sell or rent annclusionary Unit only to a Household which:
    Has provided a Certification of Income, Affordability, and Housing Size,btained from a Certifying Entity, that complies with the requirements of thisection; and

      (b)
      Has executed and provided a Declaration of Eligibility that complies withhe requirements of this section.

    A Declaration of Eligibility required by this section shall be made on a formromulgated by the Department of Housing and Community Development and shallnclude a notarized statement of the Household and sworn under penalty oferjury that:

      (a)
      The Certification of Income, Affordability, and Household Size provided tohe Owner was obtained from a Certifying Entity approved by the Department ofousing and Community Development;


      (b)
      The Household provided accurate and complete information to the Certifyingntity;


      (c)
      Each member of the Household will occupy the Inclusionary Unit as itsrincipal residence;


      (d)
      The Household does not have an ownership interest in any other housing orill divest such interest before closing on the purchase of, or signing theease for, the Inclusionary Unit;


      (e)
      The Household has satisfactorily completed a housing counseling class foromebuyers or renters approved by the Department of Housing and Communityevelopment and evidence of such satisfactory completion is attached to theeclaration of Eligibility;


      (f)
      The Household understands, its rights and obligations under the Inclusionaryovenant or lease riders required pursuant to § 2216.1; and


      (g)
      Any other representations required by the Department of Housing andommunity Development as part of the form.

    The Inclusionary Unit Owner shall provide the Inclusionary Covenant or leaseiders to the Household within ten (10) days after a request from the Household.
    A Certification of Income, Affordability, and Housing Size required by thisection means a document signed by an authorized representative of a Certifyingntity approved by the Department of Housing and Community Development,ertifying:
    The Household’s Annual Income;
    That the Household’s Annual Income qualifies it as being either a Low-Incomeousehold or Moderate-Income Household;
    That the Household’s Annual Income does not exceed the limit imposed by thenclusionary Development Covenant applicable to the Inclusionary Unit;
    The Household’s size;
    That the Household’s size is within the size range applicable to thenclusionary Unit under § 2206.3;
    For a For Sale Inclusionary Unit, that the Household will not expend more thanorty-one percent (41%) of the its Annual Income on mortgage payments,nsurance, taxes, and condominium and homeowner association fees for thepplicable Inclusionary Unit;
      and
    For a Rental Inclusionary Unit, that the Household will not expend more thanhirty-eight percent (38%) of its Annual Income on rent and utilities if notncluded in the rent for the applicable Inclusionary Unit.
